Activity: A25 – Design and implement a privacy-presing technique

Objective
The goal of this activity was to design a simple privacy-preserving technique to protect sensitive user information.

Method
I designed a data masking technique to hide sensitive information such as email addresses and phone numbers. I demonstrated this by modifying sample data to partially hide personal details while still keeping it usable.

Findings
- Sensitive information can be protected by masking parts of the data.
- This reduces the risk of exposing personal details to unauthorised users.
- The technique maintains usability while improving privacy.

Security Principle
This activity supports confidentiality by ensuring that sensitive data is not fully exposed.

Evidence
photo in evidence folder

Reflection
This activity showed that simple techniques like data masking can effectively improve privacy without complex implementation.
